	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmm, I've been away too long, I can tell.<br><br>STA is an important stat, but I still disagree with it being the most important stat.&nbsp;&nbsp;At lvl 60 now, with a few really good items, but nothing top end, I now Raid at 255 STA and 255 STR with 170 INT.  I'm a DE who put only 5 extra points into STA at creation but the Velius and Higher armors out there are just increadable.  I went from being at around 100 unbuffes STA to 173 unbuffed Stamina in about 3 levels once I started hunting in the right places.  When you add Shaman buffs to that you get maxed STA easily, and I still hit the 1250 soft cap for AC all the time, with or without a shield.<br><br>What I can't get higher without loosing alot of AC is INT.  It's a nice stat but not worth loosing the AC for, so I buy KEI ever time I pass through Nexus.  As for the mana cost of spells, they continue to increase in cost till lvl 60, then lvl 61 on we get a few spells with reduced mana (Festering Darkeness is almost half the mana of the lvl 60 darkenss).  We also get Zeffers Bite to recover mana during fights, the Clerics love us for this too.<br><br>A few people have already said it, 'Starting Stats mean very little'.  In the end, the only real difference will be the players skill.  But for right now, what I have over any Ogre or Troll is that I have about 50 extra INT over them (for more mana), with all the HP's.  Humans, Gnomes, Iksar can all end up maxing STA with very high mana pools, Erudites would have to work harder at the STA, but with the right choices they might still get 255 STA with even more mana.  Ogres and Trolls will have to work alot harder to get their INT up while perserving their AC/STA.  INT gear just doesn't seem to have a balance of AC on it mostly.<br><br>As for Flowing Thought items, there are very few out there that a Tank should wear.  They have very low AC and almost nothing else for useful stats.  The exception is the earring you get for thre Protection of the Cabbage quest, I have that one and the stats are great for any Hybred.  Otherwise you are loosing alot more than you gain from most Flowing thought items.<br><br>Just my thought after having been gone too long from posting here.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 60 DE Gravelord</td></tr>
