	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good to see you back...although you are smoking some crack or something...&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br><br>At 65, with planar power (&quot;pp&quot;), max STA is now 305, without pp, 280.  That means with boar, you need to hit 245 (with) or 220 (without) sta to max it.  A small race acquiring that is not an easy thing to do.  You will need to be in a guild that is ssra/emp capable to do that (in general).  That means that you have lots of people that will be with you, also desiring / meriting loot. It is not easy to get the items that are needed to hit that level.<br><br>Perhaps Im mis-interpreting your post, but 173 unbuffed sta plus 60 = 233, which is still a far cry of max sta for even just a lvl 60 SK (255).  Perhaps I am not understanding your comment though or your STA is higher than that unbuffed.<br><br>For a tank class, which an SK is, without a shadow of a doubt, HP, and, to a certain extent, AC, are &gt; ALL.  I challenge you or anyone else out there, to find a single top-end SK that doesnt have his STA maxxed out (or cannot max it out via boar).  The reason?  Its given, essentially, the highest priority.  If they wanted to max out say CHA or INT or any other stat, they probably could, but at the expense of other very valuable stats.  The point is, its generally recognized as the stat with the most weight.<br><br>I have had this argument all to many times.  Some of the scariest SKs I have seen on any server would argue that they would put all starting points into INT, regardless of race, as they can max their STA easily, but they cant max INT, even with c5.  That is the linchpin of their argument; they cant max INT, but they can max STA.  It has nothing to do with INT being a *superior* stat though.<br><br>For all relevant purposes, more INT is *only* really useful for high-end raiding situations, where you want to do sustained DPS over time via casting.  It has absolutely nothing to do with the normal xp grind or helping an SK solo.  Mana regen is the ticket for xp grind or soloing, not mana pool.<br><br>Dont just take my word for it.  Do your own testing.  Go fite in PoV/PoS/BoT/HoH, etc for like 2 hrs without c3 then do it with c3.  The difference is monumental, and it has essentially nothing to do with the increase in your mana pool or INT/WIS.  Its all about the mana regen.<br><br>Same thing for STA.  Discussions regarding who will MT in a group seem focused now on your total HP, CS3, CA3, AC (to a lesser extent), and just plain being able to hold agro (SK/PLD).  I have to add in the fact that I have SA3 too (a 195 lifetap proc is fairly nice to have), which is terrific in both groups and in raids.<br><br>Also, your comment about FT items couldnt be more wrong (sorry).  There are quite a few items that a *tank* (should say SK/PLD) would want to wear.  Perhaps you should look at some of the FT items out there my friend, as many have terrific HP/AC on them.<br><br>Of course, as mentioned above, you dont want to tank your HP/AC to get it, but I would add as many FT items as I possibly could.  Even a gank as simple as THO seemingly takes forever and the more mana I have throughout the fight, the better, to say nothing about how much that will help in the normal xp grind.  You REALLY OUGHT to re-think that comment.  Crown of Narandi and THO helm are really nice items, and earring of solstice is nice too.  Burrower BP is great, but, as an SK, you are going to have a tough time getting it, but I should as hell would consider wearing that, although its hard to argue against Vindy/Statue BP.  There are a bunch of items out there with FT on them, but many, granted, are hard to get a hold of.  That, however, does NOT mean that &quot;there are very few [FT items] that a Tank should wear&quot;...<br><br>Additionally, you made another comment that I hear echoed commonly that just isnt very accurate.  That being that gear nowadays just doesnt have both a nice AC/HP on it, while still giving nice INT buffs.  Check out some of the profiles of uber SKs once again.  You will see *lots* of gear on it having both nice AC and INT on them (belt of dwarf slaying, shield of mental fortitude, etc).<br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
